Enum ReactionRule.Multiplicity

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ReactionRule.Multiplicity>
      • fr.insa.rennes.info.chemical.user.ReactionRule.Multiplicity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ReactionRule.Multiplicity>
    Enclosing interface:
    ReactionRule

    public static enum ReactionRule.Multiplicity
extends java.lang.Enum<ReactionRule.Multiplicity>
    Enumerates the different possible multiplicities for a reaction.

    ONE_SHOT indicates that the reaction will happen only once, the ReactionRule will then be removed from the solution.

    INFINITY_SHOT indicates that the reaction will always happen if reactives are present, until solution inertia. Contrary to OneShot, the ReactionRule will not be removed from the solution after reaction.
